<br>
Ok my biggest problem atm, is this:<br>
<br>
With the new patch parry,evade and blocking work awesome now. its spectactular! however this patch screws over the formula DW/CD in a very unique way. when i style with DW/CD my rigth hand lands and hits for the extra dmg and etc, but my offhand is constantly parried/blocked/evaded. constantly. so when i do swing both weapons which is a measily 6/10 times, my hand is constantly parried/blocked/evaded or misses. <br>
<br>
What i want is a offhand 'to hit bonus' when using DW/CD styles at the minimum, and really i'm not asking for much.<br>
<br>
This would also make DW/CD styles more appealing.<br>
<br>
i like to think of Mercs/Blademasters as arm wrestlers. our right hand is big and strong and hits for alotto dmg, while our left hand is small and pathetic looking, where it is blocked and parried and etc with ease.... when we do swing the left hand.  now that parry and all that has been changed to work now, making DW/CD work is what i want.<br>
<br>
On a side note i think a base base to swing 6/10 times is quite low if a merc/blademaster specced to 50 in DW/CD. a Merc/BM should have a 75% chance to dw witha  50 spec.... however in asking this i'm sure mythic would find it quite unreasonable to do this, for some reason. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
in conclusion i was wondering if anyone else would want to fight for this? and send mythic regarding these issues? i persoanlly feel theya re rather important issues to address, along with the stun fix for dwers on pend. <br>
<br>
evidently i'm told mythic  sometimes does listen<br>
